Former Chair of the Equal Employment Opportunity Commission, Jacqueline Berrien, has passed away. President Obama and First Lady Michelle Obama expressed their sadness at the news and praised Berrien's leadership and dedication to ensuring equal opportunities in the workplace. Berrien's career was marked by her work at the NAACP Legal Defense and Educational Fund and the American Civil Liberties Union, where she fought for underrepresented communities. During her time at the EEOC, she revitalized the commission and focused on protecting the fundamental rights of all Americans. The President and First Lady offered their gratitude for Berrien's service and extended their condolences to her loved ones.